high-rate `sensor_gyro_fifo` stream and the EKF-side `vehicle_imu`. It does **not**
plot `vehicle_angular_velocity` â€” the *filtered* angular rate the rate controller
actually runs on (post software LPF/notch). That signal is exactly what matters for
diagnosing whether vibration is leaking into the control loop, so we want the same
time-series + spectrum views for it.

Verified in the log (`log_1_2026-4-29-13-48-36.ulg`):
- Topic `vehicle_angular_velocity`, single instance (`multi_id=0`), 26711 rows.
- Fields: `xyz[0..2]` (rad/s, filtered rate), `xyz_derivative[0..2]` (we use only `xyz`).
- `timestamp_sample` Î”t â‰ˆ 1.497 ms â†’ fs â‰ˆ 668 Hz (plenty for an FFT).

User decision: produce **two separate PNGs**, exactly mirroring the gyro FIFO plots
(not a combined figure):
- `imu_gyro_vehicle_angular_velocity_mag.png` â€” X/Y/Z time series.
- `imu_fft_gyro_vehicle_angular_velocity.png` â€” X/Y/Z FFT PSD.

## Changes â€” `analyze_imu_vibration.py`

### 1. New function: time series (mirrors `plot_fifo_magnitude_timeseries`, gyro branch)
Add near the other magnitude-timeseries functions (after `plot_vehicle_imu_magnitude_timeseries`, ~line 423).

- Get topic via `get_topic(ulog, "vehicle_angular_velocity")`; if `None`, print skip and return.
- `t = t_seconds(d, ulog)`, `scale = RAD_TO_DEG`.
- `fig, axes = plt.subplots(3, 1, figsize=(12, 9), sharex=True)`.
- For `k` in 0..2 plot `d.data[f"xyz[{k}]"] * scale` with the **identical style**:
  `color="steelblue", label="vehicle_angular_velocity", linewidth=0.4, alpha=0.6`.
- Per-axis: `ax.set_ylabel(f"gyro {axis_name} (deg/s)")`, `legend(loc="upper right", fontsize=8)`, `grid(True, alpha=0.3)`.
- `axes[-1].set_xlabel("time (s)")`, `suptitle("vehicle_angular_velocity per-axis time series")`, `tight_layout()`.
- Save to `outdir / "imu_gyro_vehicle_angular_velocity_mag.png"`, dpi=120, `plt.close(fig)`, print confirmation.

### 2. New function: FFT PSD (mirrors `fft_around_event` gyro branch)
Add after the new time-series function.

- Get topic; if `None`, skip/return.
- `t = t_seconds(d, ulog)`, `scale = RAD_TO_DEG`, `mask = (t >= t0) & (t <= t1)`.
- If `mask.sum() < 256`: print skip and return (same threshold as `fft_around_event`).
- `fs` from the window: `dt_pub = float(np.median(np.diff(t[mask])))` (vehicle_angular_velocity
  has no `dt` field, so derive it from sample spacing like `fft_vehicle_imu` does, line 350);
  guard `dt_pub <= 0`; `fs = 1.0 / dt_pub`.
- Per-axis data: `d.data[f"xyz[{k}]"][mask] * scale`.
- `fig, axes = plt.subplots(3, 1, figsize=(11, 9), sharex=True)`; for each axis:
  - `freqs, _, psd = direct_fft(axis_data, fs)` (reuse existing helper, line 132).
  - `ax.plot(freqs, psd, color="steelblue", linewidth=0.8)`.
  - `annotate_top_peaks(ax, freqs, psd, n_peaks=6)` (line 159).
  - `ax.set_ylabel(f"{axis_name} PSD (deg/s)Â²/Hz")` (matches `fft_around_event` gyro ylabel).
  - `ax.grid(True, which="both", alpha=0.3)`, `ax.set_xlim(0, fs / 2)`.
  - `if show_lpf: add_lpf_lines(ax, "gyro", fs)` (line 177 â€” draws IMU_GYRO_CUTOFF/IMU_DGYRO_CUTOFF + Nyquist).
  - `ax.legend(loc="upper right", fontsize=7)`.
- `axes[-1].set_xlabel("Frequency (Hz)")`,
  `suptitle(f"FFT PSD (flat-top) of vehicle_angular_velocity gyro, fs={fs:.0f} Hz")`, `tight_layout()`.
- Save to `outdir / "imu_fft_gyro_vehicle_angular_velocity.png"`, dpi=120, `plt.close(fig)`, print confirmation.

